div.p:
6. Pag. 32. You say [
                  Doth he say a word of owning Parish Churches, and Worship.
               ] Ans. If you or he say nothing against these, we shall leave the Diocesan case to others: But if you be the man that I have lately privately written to, I doubt not but I have proved to you, that Parish Churches that have good Ministers, are true particular Churches, and those Ministers true Pastors, and that any Bishops holding the contrary, doth not disprove it.
